cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.HC, cs.CL 

The paper focuses on understanding the factors that contribute to the popularity of events in event-based social networks. This involves analyzing contextual factors such as spatial, group, temporal, and semantic features, as well as social influence networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Computational Social Science). Additionally, the paper involves modeling and prediction, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper also touches on human behavior analysis, which could fall under cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
